  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F.",
    "In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, ginger, and garlic.",
    "Add ssamjang, fish sauce, and honey to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Drizzle coconut oil over the top and sprinkle with sesame seeds.",
    "Double-fry KFC chicken pieces and chop them into smaller pieces.",
    "Place the chicken on top of the vegetable mixture.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes or until the top is golden brown.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped green onions if desired.",
    "Let sit for 5 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld together."
